      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C (160°C fan). Grease two 20 cm round cake tins and line the bases with baking paper. Beat {{unsalted-butter}} and {{caster-sugar}} together for 4 to 5 minutes until pale and noticeably fluffy. Add {{vanilla-extract}}, then beat in the {{eggs}} one at a time, adding a tablespoon of the measured {{self-raising-flour}} with each egg if the mixture starts to curdle. Sift in the remaining {{self-raising-flour}} and {{baking-powder}} and fold in gently with a large spoon, stop as soon as the flour disappears. Divide between the tins and smooth the tops. Bake for 20 to 22 minutes until risen and a skewer inserted in the centre comes out clean. The cakes should spring back when lightly pressed.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cool and assemble",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Leave the cakes in their tins for 5 minutes before turning out onto a wire rack. Leave to cool completely before filling. Beat the filling {{unsalted-butter}}, {{icing-sugar}}, and {{vanilla-extract}} until smooth. Spread the {{raspberry-jam}} over the flat side of the bottom layer, then the buttercream on top of the jam. Place the second sponge on top. Dust with {{icing-sugar}} just before serving.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
